A former Fortune 500 executive has admitted that he killed a pregnant woman and her fiancé when he tried to kill himself by driving his pickup truck across a highway median into oncoming traffic.

Robert Dellinger, 54, pleaded guilty on Thursday to negligent homicide for the deaths of 24-year-old Amanda Murphy and 29-year-old Jason Timmons, of Wilder, Vermont. 

He also pleaded guilty to assault for the death of their fetus. Murphy was eight months pregnant.

Dellinger, of Sunapee, New Hampshire, was initially charged with manslaughter, but that was later upgraded to second-degree murder. 

