Dellinger, who suffered cuts on his head and face, was initially charged with two counts of reckless manslaughter.

Miss Murphy, 24, was excited to be a mother for the first time, and the couple had already named their unborn baby girl Reagan Elizabeth.

A week before the crash, the residential center where the couple worked together hosted a baby shower for them.

Catherine Amarante, executive director at the facility, described the couple as 'very loving'.

