Mr Timmons, 29, was also a father to three children from a previous relationship. 

According to prosecution, the former executive had argued with his wife over his 
medications on the morning of the crash, WMUR reported.

'He was driving around, depressed and loopy,' senior assistant attorney general for New Hampshire Susan Morrell said. 'He saw the median and decided to turn into it.' 

Dellinger's lawyer, R. Peter Decato, 
however called the state's comments 'over the top' and said Dellinger had led a 
'productive and exemplary life.'

The married father had served as senior vice president and chief financial officer at Fortune 500 company PPG Industries Inc.

